{
  "stem": "20083.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at first, as you can imagine, it was very, very difficult.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even though I had a basic knowledge of English, it really didn't help me very much at first at least because the teachers had their own different accents which were intelligible maybe to the rest of the school but not to me, including the horrible language action-- accent.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, and we even had one cockney teacher.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it took me a few-- I would say about a couple more months before I could really get adjusted to all of these different accents and begin to grasp what they were teaching us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the life in school was-- after I'd really gotten used to everything-- it was sheer heaven.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I loved every second of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Not only because I could start learning again, but all the students, except one of them, were wonderful in every respect.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They tried to be my friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They helped me whenever they could or when I didn't understand something or lost my way on the huge grounds there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They helped me find my way around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Except this one boy-- I cannot remember, very tall boy-- was actually a Nazi and a great anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he often made anti-Jewish remarks right in front of me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then he was actually talked down by some of the other students telling him to shut up or mind your own business or get out of here.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But otherwise, I say it was quite wonderful.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was more like a country life because it was right in Dorset in the country.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And as I mentioned before, it was a Duke-- a former Duke's home, a huge place of about, I would say, between 100 and 150 rooms, which were later converted into classrooms and dormitories.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
